headline: Johan Grahn Joins Raymond James Investment Management as Head of ETFs
summary: ST. PETERSBURG, Fla., Aug. 28, 2025 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- Raymond James Investment Management, a global asset management company with $114.7 billion in assets and a wholly-owned subsidiary of Raymond James, has appointed Johan Grahn as Head of Exchange-Traded Funds (ETFs). In this role, Grahn will work with Matt Johnson, Head of Product and Marketing, and Susan Walzer, President of the firm's Family of Funds, in the continued development of Raymond James Investment Management’s ETF offerings.
